			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Currently chrome looks for the bitcode Hash in the NaCl manifest file.

However, this means that nmf files must be autogenerated (currently done by pnacl-nmf.py, and the official SDK's official generate_manifest.py does not know about this).

The bitcode file header also contains a hash, which Derek added.  We could use that to simplify the NMF.

If we do that, we need to consider how much of the bitcode file to download / pull from the chrome cache.  Currently, we only download the small NMF if we have a cache hit, and avoid downloading the bitcode.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-06-18T20:28:54.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-08-24T19:58:31.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
